title: Iran nuclear deal hits milestone aimed at sanctions relief
text: Photo: Ebrahim Noroozi, AP Iranian Foreign Minister Mohammad Javad Zarif speaks during the Munich Security Conference in Tehran, Iran, Saturday, Oct. 17, 2015. Iranian Foreign Minister Mohammad Javad Zarif speaks during the... WASHINGTON (AP) — The U.S. expects Iran will take months to live up to its end of a seven-nation nuclear pact that could eventually provide the country relief from international sanctions.
